The paper discusses the application of neural attention models on sequence classification tasks such as dialogue act detection and key term extraction. These tasks are commonly associated with natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the computer science sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves text analysis and information retrieval, which could place it under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and software development (cs.SD).
